==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Public-spirited
<hw>Pub"lic-spir`it*ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having, or exercising, a disposition to advance the interest of the
community or public; <as>as, <ex>public-spirited</ex>
men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dictated by a regard to public good; <as>as, a
<ex>public-spirited</ex> project or measure</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pub"lic-spir`it*ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pub"lic-spir`it*ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

